-- Boeing says proposed 787 fix is long-term, not interim step
-- 
-- Wed Feb 27, 2013 10:36pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/02/28/us-boeing-dreamliner-solution-idUSBRE91R06G20130228

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Boeing Co ( BA.N ) said on Thursday that its proposed fix to its grounded 787 Dreamliner passenger jets takes into account the risk of a battery fire and overheating risks. 
 Boeing Commercial Airplanes CEO Ray Conner told reporters after meeting Japan's Transport Minister Akihiro Ota the proposed solution was a long-term plan, not an interim fix. (Reporting by  James Topham  and  Mari Saito )